      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. so if i have a really long overhang, the torque gets massive right? what happens if the design is slightly off or if an unexpected heavy load is placed right on the tip? like how does that sudden increase in force affect the stability of the internal connection point?",
      "source": "evaluator"
